column3: VII Bieg na Kampus FAIS UJ (5k)
Longer run w 2nd half surges (6x 30sec @3min/km w 2min recoveries)
column5:
Surges felt great!! It's nice to see that cadence over 185 at speed.  I tried a new post run isotonic too, it might be the new go-to for me.

I don't know if it's because of the higher temps the past few days, but my heart-rate data has been really off sometimes. In those cases I'll be hiding the data so as not to be misleading anyone, especially myself ;)

column3: Easy paced run with second half fartleks

column5:
Its getting warm out there!
But the heat notwithstanding this was an extremely satisfying run on at least 2 fronts:
First, I finally got some HR data that isn't complete rubbish, and I was happy to see it holding steady in the 170s at that pace.
Second, an average cadence of 170 at easy pace is a huge breakthrough for me.  Maybe I'm finally getting off of my heels and my body positioned for more efficient running.  I think the next few weeks are really going to tell the tale.

Whew! What a workout for a Wednesday! Glad I got out there before it got really hot! It was warm enough as it was, but fortunately there was a headwind on the sunny side which made it bearable.  I can't believe that's already almost 500k on the Altra Escalante 1.0s, I'm really psyched for my new Torin 3.0s to arrive and start sharing the miles (or kms).

column3: Easy paced longer run w Ala

column5: I really wasn't planning to run today, but my Altra Torin 3.0s arrived and I just couldn't resist a test drive.

Man oh man the heat was getting to me. 30C or 86F for the Americans out there ;)  I planned to throw in some surges on the return, but it became obvious that just getting back home would be enough of a challenge today.
So damn fun! I am lovin the Torin's, no doubts.  Sadly, I don't think I can claim the HR data on this one as accurate.
Felt great!!
Hot out there!

It was still pretty warm out there which may account for the elevated heart rate.  Also, the increased km's on this new training plan are going to take some getting used to.  At this moment it's not obvious if my body is going to be able to cope with it.

Just about rounded off a 70km training week.  The 1st of 16 weeks leading up to the Krakow 1/2 Marathon.  Glad to see continual improvements in cardiovascular fitness.  Can't wait to see how next week goes :)
LongSlowDistance for the win!

column3: Easy paced (mostly) recon mission for the Zakrzówek 10k

column5: These recovery runs after more serious workouts always feel really hard. My legs feel like concrete and my heartrate seems artificially high. But I really think the kms (or miles) on these days are some of the most important of the week.

What a beautiful day for a long run!  Overall, I'm really happy with the pace, cadence, and heartrate.  Going to start a bit of taper before the 10k next weekend. It's a slightly hilly trail race, so I'm not expecting a PB, but it should be fun at any rate.

Really trying to take it easy before the race on Sunday, while still getting in a few good kms.  I started having some calf cramps again today, but not nearly so badly as a few weeks ago. Has anyone else had a similar problem? What did you do to for it? Hydration? Foam rolling? Magnesium and Potassium? I'm trying it all!!

28th place overall!! I'm pretty happy with that result.  43:26 official time would even be a PB for a 10k race if the course weren't a bit short :P
